===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|日|京|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=sun}}. Originally, it meant "sunlight". Compare [[昜]].

===Etymology 1===
Possibly {{der|zh|sit}}. Probably related to {{och-l|鏡|mirror}} and {{och-l|影|shadow}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}). STEDT compares it to {{cog|tbq-kuk-pro|*klaaŋ-I}}, {{m|tbq-kuk-pro|*klaan-II||to shine; light; bright}} and lists {{och-l|亮|bright}}, {{och-l|陽|sunshine}}, {{och-l|章|emblem; to display}} as additional comparanda.

